Package neureka.backend.api.algorithms

Class AbstractBaseAlgorithm<C extends Algorithm<C>>

java.lang.Object
neureka.backend.api.algorithms.AbstractBaseAlgorithm<C>
Type Parameters:
C - The type of the concrete extension of this class.
All Implemented Interfaces:
Algorithm<C>, ADAgentSupplier, BackwardADPredicate, ExecutionDispatcher, ExecutionPreparation, ForwardADPredicate, SuitabilityPredicate
Direct Known Subclasses:
AbstractFunctionalAlgorithm, FallbackAlgorithm
public abstract class AbstractBaseAlgorithm<C extends Algorithm<C>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Algorithm<C>
This is a partial implementation of the Algorithm interface which implements the component system for implementation instances of the ImplementationFor interface. These components implement an algorithm for a specific Algorithm.

    • setImplementationFor

      public <D extends Device<?>,​ E extends ImplementationFor<D>> C setImplementationFor​(java.lang.Class<D> deviceClass, E implementation)
      Description copied from interface: Algorithm
      Implementations of the Algorithm interface ought to express a compositional design pattern.
      This means that concrete implementations of an algorithm for a device are not extending an Algorithm, they are components of it instead.
      These components can be stored on an Algorithm by passing a Device class as key and an ImplementationFor instance as value.
      Specified by:
      setImplementationFor in interface Algorithm<C extends Algorithm<C>>
      Type Parameters:
      D - The type parameter of the Device type for which an implementation should be set in this Device.
      E - The type of the ImplementationFor the provided Device type.
      Parameters:
      deviceClass - The class of the Device for which an implementation should be set.
      implementation - The ImplementationFor the provided Device type.
      Returns:
      This very Algorithm instance to allow for method chaining.
